        jTextArea1.setText("-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n-------------------------------------- SING IN ------------------------------------------\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n - In the first of the fields the user is entered and in the second the password.\n - To establish connection, press the \"Sing in\" button.\n - In order to carry out the action, both fields must be filled in.\n - If any of the fields does not match any of the registered users, the window \"bad \n   login!\" will display the error \"We couldn't recognize this account\".\n - If the fields are correct, the user's calendar will be accessed.\n\n\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n-------------------------------------- SING UP ------------------------------------------\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n - In order to sing up, it is necessary to fill in all the fields, correctly.\n - If any of the fields does not meet the requirements, it will show an error window\n   \"Wrong input!\"\n - To select between a student account and a teacher account, it will be done through the\n   drop down.\n - The password to create a teacher account must be correct or the \"sing up\" button\n   It wont be available.\n - To return to the log in window, press the button located at the top\n   left.\n - To sing up, if all the fields are correct, the button \"Create\n   account\"\n - Possible mistakes:\n     - The \"Name\" field must be between 3 and 15 characters long.\n     - The \"Surname\" field must be between 3 and 20 characters long.\n     - The \"DNI\" field must be 9 characters long.\n     - The \"Username\" field must be between 5 and 25 characters long.\n     - The \"Email\" field must be between 5 and 50 characters long.\n     - The \"Password\" and \"Confirm Password\" fields must match. They must also meet\n       that the length is between 5 and 25.\n\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n-------------------------------------- ALUMNO -------------------------------------------\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n - Change the week:\n     It will be done through the buttons located in the upper left part,\n     \"Previous\" to access previous weeks and \"Next\" to access weeks\n     later.\n     The date of that week is just above the calendar.\n\n\n - View profile:\n     In the \"Account\" menu, located at the top left, select the option \"My Account\".\n     It displays all the user information as well as other possible actions:\n\n     - Change password:\n         (Inside My Account)\n         First you must press the \"Change Password\" button and then proceed to fill in \n         the fields the fields shown.\n         All fields must be filled in and must be correct.\n         To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n\n         Possible mistakes:\n          - The \"Current Password\" field must match the current password.\n          - The \"New Password\" and \"Confirm new Password\" fields must match.\n            They must also meet that the length is between 5 and 25.\n          - The new password cannot match the current one.\n\n     - Change email:\n         (Inside My Account)\n         First you must press the \"Change email\" button and then the new one will be \n         written email address.\n         All fields must be filled in and must be correct.\n         To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n\n         Possible mistakes:\n          - The \"New email\" field must be between 5 and 50 characters long to\n            be correct.\n\n     - Delete account:\n         (Inside My Account)\n         You must press the \"Delete account\" button.\n\n - Create activity:\n     In the \"Edit\" menu, located at the top left, the option \"Create Activity\".\n     All fields (except \"Comments\" and \"Color\") must be filled in correctly.\n     To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n\n     Possible mistakes:\n      - The \"Name\" field must be between 5 and 50 characters long.\n      - The \"Date\" field must be in the format yyyy-mm-dd (year-month-day).\n      - The \"Start hour\" field must be in the format hh:mm:ss (hour:minute:second).\n      - The \"End hour\" field must be in the format hh:mm:ss (hour:minute:second).\n      - The \"Comments\" field must be less than 500 characters.\n\n - Edit activity:\n     In the \"Edit\" menu, located at the top left, the option \"Edit Activity\".\n     All fields (except \"Comments\" and \"Color\") must be filled out.\n     First it is necessary to select the activity to edit in the Activities drop-down\n     menu.\n     To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n\n     Possible mistakes:\n         - The \"Date\" field must be in the format yyyy-mm-dd (year-month-day).\n         - The \"Start hour\" field must be in the format hh:mm:ss (hour:minute:second).\n         - The \"End hour\" field must be in the format hh:mm:ss (hour:minute:second).\n         - The \"Comments\" field must be less than 500 characters.\n\n - Remove activity:\n     In the \"Edit\" menu, located at the top left, the option \"Remove Activity\".\n     Select the activity you want to delete in the \"Ativities\" drop-down menu and then \n     press the \"Remove Activity\" button.\n     To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n\n - Select Subjects:\n     In the \"Edit\" menu, located at the top left, the option \"Select Subject\".\n     Two possible actions related to subjects:\n         - Join subject:\n             In order to join to a new subject, choose in the drop-down menu a subject \n             and then press the \"Join\" button.\n\n         - Leave subject:\n             In order to leave a subject, choose in the drop-down menu that subject and \n             then press the \"Leave\" button.\n     To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n\n - Select group:\n     In the \"Edit\" menu, located at the top left, the option \"Select Group\".\n     First, choose the subject in the \"Subject\" drop-down menu. Second, select the group\n     you want to enter and then press the \"Select\" button to save the changes.\n     To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n\n - Access help:\n     In the \"Account\" menu, located at the top left, the option will be selected \"Help\".\n     It can also be accessed by pressing \"F1\".\n\n - Change calendar:\n     The selection is made through the drop-down menu located to the right of the\n     week change buttons.\n \n - Log out:\n     The \"Log out\" button located in the upper right corner is pressed.\n     It can also be done through the \"Account\" menu or by pressing \"Alt + F4\".\n\n\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n------------------------------------- PROFESOR ------------------------------------------\n-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n - Change the week:\n     It will be done through the buttons located in the upper left part, \"Previous\" to \n     access previous weeks and \"Next\" to access later weeks.\n     The date of that week is just above the calendar.\n\n - View profile:\n     In the \"Account\" menu, located at the top left, the option will be selected \"My \n     Account\".\n     It displays all the user information as well as other possible actions:\n\n     - Change password:\n         (Inside My Account)\n         First you must press the \"Change Password\" button and then proceed to fill in \n         the fields the fields shown.\n         All fields must be filled in and must be correct.\n         To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n\n         Possible mistakes:\n          - The \"Current Password\" field must match the current password.\n          - The \"New Password\" and \"Confirm new Password\" fields must match.\n            They must also meet that the length is between 5 and 25.\n          - The new password cannot match the current one.\n\n     - Change email:\n         (Inside My Account)\n         First you must press the \"Change email\" button and then the new one will be written\n         email address.\n         All fields must be filled in and must be correct.\n         To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n\n         Possible mistakes:\n          - The \"New email\" field must be between 5 and 50 characters long to\n            be correct.\n\n     - Delete account:\n         (Inside My Account)\n         You must press the \"Delete account\" button.\n\n \n - Create activity:\n     In the \"Edit\" menu, located at the top left, the option \"Create Activity\".\n     Depending on the type of activity chosen, certain information will have to be \n     specified:\n      - Lecture: the group to which it is taught must be specified.\n      - Meeting: you must specify the teacher with whom you have the meeting.\n      - Tutorship: the student who attends the tutoring must be specified.\n\n     All fields (except \"Comments\" and \"Color\") must be filled out.\n     To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n\n     Possible mistakes:\n      - The \"Name\" field must be between 5 and 50 characters long.\n      - The \"Date\" field must be in the format yyyy-mm-dd (year-month-day).\n      - The \"Start hour\" field must be in the format hh:mm:ss (hour:minute:second).\n      - The \"End hour\" field must be in the format hh:mm:ss (hour:minute:second).\n      - The \"Comments\" field must be less than 500 characters.\n      - The \"Classroom\" field must have 5 characters.\n\n - Edit activity:\n     In the \"Edit\" menu, located at the top left, the option \"Edit Activity\".\n     All fields (except \"Comments\" and \"Color\") must be filled out.\n     First it is necessary to select the activity to edit in the Activities drop-down\n     menu.\n     As in create activity, depending on the type of activity chosen, certain\n     information will have to be specified:\n      - Lecture: the group to which it is taught must be specified.\n      - Meeting: you must specify the teacher with whom you have the meeting.\n      - Tutorship: the student who attends the tutoring must be specified.\n\n     To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n\n     Possible mistakes:\n         - The \"Date\" field must be in the format yyyy-mm-dd (year-month-day).\n         - The \"Start hour\" field must be in the format hh:mm:ss (hour:minute:second).\n         - The \"End hour\" field must be in the format hh:mm:ss (hour:minute:second).\n         - The \"Comments\" field must be less than 500 characters.\n         - The \"Classroom\" field must have 5 characters.\n\n - Delete activity:\n     In the \"Edit\" menu, located at the top left, the option \"Remove Activity\".\n     Select the activity you want to delete in the \"Ativities\" drop-down menu and then \n     the \"Remove Activity\" button is pressed.\n     To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n \n - Select subjects:\n     In the \"Edit\" menu, located at the top left, the option \"Select Subject\".\n     Two possible actions related to subjects:\n         - Join subject:\n             In order to join to a new subject, choose in the drop-down menu a subject \n             and then press the \"Join\" button.\n\n         - Leave subject:\n             In order to leave a subject, choose in the drop-down menu that subject and \n             then press the \"Leave\" button.\n\n     To exit the window press the button in the upper left corner.\n\n - Manage group:\n     (In the \"Edit\" menu select \"Manage Groups\" option)\n     First choose the subject in the \"Subject\" drop-down menu. Second, select the group \n     you want to operate with.\n     Two operations are possible:\n         - Create group:\n             First choose the subject in the \"Subject\" drop-down menu. Then, press\n             \"Create Group\" button and give the new group a name in \"Name\" field and a \n             type.\n         - Remove:\n          Once a subject and one of it's group are selected press \"Remove\" button.\n\n     To exit the window, press the button in the upper left corner\n\n - Access help:\n     In the \"Account\" menu, located at the top left, the option will be selected \"Help\".\n     It can also be accessed by pressing \"F1\".\n   \n - Change calendar:\n     The selection is made through the drop-down menu located to the right of the\n     week change buttons.\n \n - Manage Accounts:\n     In order to manage other users accounts, \"Manage Account\" button, located next to \n     the calendar, must be pressed. Once the \"Manage account\" window appears, select an \n     user in the drop-down menu and press \"Manage\" button. \n     The user profile will pop up as well as the information and the possible actions. \n     (see View Profile).\n\n     To exit the window, press the button in the upper left corner\n\n - Log out:\n     The \"Log out\" button located in the upper right corner is pressed.\n     It can also be done through the \"Account\" menu or by pressing \"Alt + F4\".\n");
